result.execSummary:
The defendant David William LaBarge was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take Vehicle w/o Consent and Use of Force, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(1r).
  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

9:58 AM Defendant David William LaBarge in court, in custody.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for David William LaBarge.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Agent Jennifer Sem in court for Department of Corrections. Court calls case. State makes argument. Potential for up to 15 years in prison. Cites circumstances of the charges. Cites 15 prior criminal convictions. Medium risk to reoffend. Probation not appropriate, would unduly depreciate offense. Believes this is a prison sentence. State recommends on Count 2, 7 years, 4 years IC, 3 years ES, on Counts 3 and 5, 9 months each count, all concurrent with one another, 205 days credit, Eligible for release programs. Court costs, DOC programming, no contact with Victim. There is a restitution claim for $9652.92. Restitution not stipulated. May need restitution hearing. 
Attorney Anderson makes argument. Recommend withheld for 3 years probation, 9 months of conditional jail, restitution, court costs, 9 months on misdemeanor counts, concurrent and concurrent to the felony count. Cites circumstances of the charges. Defendant is not minimizing his actions. Should have opportunity to prove he can succeed on probation.  
Defendant makes statements.
Court makes statements on charges and sentencing. Has been placed on probation 3 times in the past and has been revoked twice. Probation would unduly depreciate offense. 
Court orders on Count 2, 4 years IC, 3 years ES, on counts 3 and 5 9 months jail each count, concurrent on each count and to count 2, costs, 205 days credit, DOC programming, no contact with Victim. Eligible for both programs. 
Parties address restitution. State would like a restitution hearing set. Court sets date for restitution hearing.  Defendant may appear via zoom, if necessary.
Restitution hearing scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

12:58 PM Defendant David William LaBarge in court.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for David William LaBarge. Court calls case. Court has been provided with plea questionnaire. State indicates will plead to Count 2, 3 and 5 in 22CF1, remaining counts will be dismissed but read in. 21CM356 will be dismissed but read in. PSI to be ordered. State will cap at 4 years IC, 3 years ES, not opposed to programming.
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest to all counts. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and knowingly made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered. All remaining charges are dismissed but read in.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.
